<Window xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        x:Class="VirtTermMac.Views.MainWindow"
        Title="VirtTermMac"
        SizeToContent="WidthAndHeight"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterScreen">
    <!--
        Content is built entirely in code-behind (MainWindow.axaml.cs),
        mirroring VirtTerm's WinForms MainForm — the menu is dynamically
        generated (DynamicMenuBuilder) and the terminal control's size is
        determined at runtime from font metrics, so there's nothing
        meaningful to declare statically here.

        SizeToContent="WidthAndHeight" is the fix for the editor being cut
        off at the top/right: without it, Avalonia opens the window at an
        arbitrary default size instead of sizing to fit the 80x25 terminal
        grid + menu + status bar, so the Fill-docked TerminalControl gets
        squeezed into less room than its 80x25 grid actually needs and the
        far edge is clipped.
    -->
</Window>
